The paper discusses the use of Artificial Intelligence (AI) and semantic web technologies to build smart IoT systems, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.AI sub-category. It also focuses on getting meaningful knowledge from sensor data, which could fall under the cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.DB (Databases) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the need for a knowledge framework and the integration of information systems, which could relate to the cs.SE (Software Engineering) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the potential economic impact and opportunities of IoT, which could fall under the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category.
